      • shutDownInSeparateProcess

        private java.lang.String shutDownInSeparateProcess()
        Spawns a separate JVM process to shut down the running server using the code distributed with the release.

        This method was added because some versions of Derby cannot be shut down using code from a newer release.

        Returns:
        An error message, or null if no errors.

      • ping

        private boolean ping(boolean exepectServerUp,
                     java.lang.Process proc)
        Pings the server.
        Parameters:
        exepectServerUp - whether the server is expected to be up or down
        proc - the process in which the server runs (may be null)
        Returns:
        Whether the ping is considered ok, which is determined by the response or lack of response from the server and the value of expectedServerUp.
